king-and-tailgating-information</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/3/baseball-ncaa-super-regional-parking-and-tailgating-information</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Tailgating at Kendrick Family Ballpark" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/6/3/WVU_V_UK_Monday-12.jpeg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – Due to heavy traffic expected in and around Kendrick Family Ballpark, WVU Athletics and West Virginia University are encouraging fans to arrive early ahead of all games in the Morgantown Super Regional.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/3/WVU_V_UK_Monday-12.jpeg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/3/WVU_V_UK_Monday-12.jpeg"><media:title>Tailgating at Kendrick Family Ballpark</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/3/WVU_V_UK_Monday-12.jpeg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Wed, 3 Jun 2026 12:20:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59160</s:story_id></item><item><title>Mountaineers Advance to College World Series</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/6/baseball-mountaineers-advance-to-college-world-series</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/6/baseball-mountaineers-advance-to-college-world-series</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="The West Virginia Baseball team poses for a photo after winning the NCAA Morgantown Super Regional" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/6/6/Morgantown_SR_G1_BSB-1230.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – For the first time in program history, the West Virginia University baseball team is going to the Men's College World Series after finishing off a two-game sweep of Cal Poly in the NCAA Super Regionals with a 17-1 victory over the Mustangs on Saturday afternoon at Kendrick Family Ballpark. The Mountaineers improve to 45-15 on the season, setting a new program record for wins.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/6/Morgantown_SR_G1_BSB-1230.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/6/Morgantown_SR_G1_BSB-1230.jpg"><media:title>The West Virginia Baseball team poses for a photo after winning the NCAA Morgantown Super Regional</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/6/Morgantown_SR_G1_BSB-1230.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sat, 6 Jun 2026 20:49:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59172</s:story_id></item><item><title>A Statement from WVU Athletics</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/6/general-a-statement-from-wvu-athletics</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/6/general-a-statement-from-wvu-athletics</guid><category>General</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="flying wv" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2023/5/8/flying_wv.png" /><br /><br />During the weather delay at today's NCAA Morgantown Super Regional baseball game, between WVU and Cal Poly, heavy winds blew an event tent over at an adjacent parking lot causing injury.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2023/5/8/flying_wv.png" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2023/5/8/flying_wv.png"><media:title>flying wv</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2023/5/8/flying_wv.png" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Sat, 6 Jun 2026 20:15:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>3</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59171</s:story_id></item><item><title>Mountaineers Take Game One of Super Regionals Against Cal Poly</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/5/baseball-mountaineers-take-game-one-of-super-regionals-against-cal-poly</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/5/baseball-mountaineers-take-game-one-of-super-regionals-against-cal-poly</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Tyrus Hall celebrates after hitting a grand slam against Cal Poly in game one of the NCAA Super Regionals" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/6/5/EEN00534.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The No. 16 West Virginia University baseball team defeated Cal Poly, 12-2, Friday afternoon at Kendrick Family Ballpark in the NCAA Super Regionals and are now one win away from its first College World Series berth in program history.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/5/EEN00534.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/5/EEN00534.jpg"><media:title>Tyrus Hall celebrates after hitting a grand slam against Cal Poly in game one of the NCAA Super Regionals</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/5/EEN00534.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Fri, 5 Jun 2026 16:33:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59168</s:story_id></item><item><title>College World Series Requests Now Available</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/5/baseball-college-world-series-requests-now-available</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/5/baseball-college-world-series-requests-now-available</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="College World Series Requests" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/6/5/Omaha_Requests_Open.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. (June 5, 2026) –  The Mountaineer Ticket Office has announced that NCAA Men's College World Series ticket requests are now available. Should the Mountaineers advance, the event will take place June 12 – 22 at Charles Schwab Field in Omaha Nebraska where the final eight Division 1 college baseball teams will compete for the national championship.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/5/Omaha_Requests_Open.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/5/Omaha_Requests_Open.jpg"><media:title>College World Series Requests</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/5/Omaha_Requests_Open.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Fri, 5 Jun 2026 17:00:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59169</s:story_id></item><item><title>Athletics To Retire Pat White’s No. 5</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/5/football-athletics-to-retire-pat-whites-no-5</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/5/football-athletics-to-retire-pat-whites-no-5</guid><category>Football</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="pat white 5" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/6/5/1920x1080PatWhite5.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – West Virginia University Vice President and Director of Athletics Wren Baker announced today that the department will retire football legend Pat White's No. 5 this fall at a home game to be determined later this summer.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/5/1920x1080PatWhite5.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/5/1920x1080PatWhite5.jpg"><media:title>pat white 5</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/5/1920x1080PatWhite5.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Fri, 5 Jun 2026 10:27:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>2</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59167</s:story_id></item><item><title>Yehl Named National Pitcher of the Year Finalist</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/4/baseball-yehl-named-national-pitcher-of-the-year-finalist</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/4/baseball-yehl-named-national-pitcher-of-the-year-finalist</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Maxx Yehl throws a pitch against Kentucky in the NCAA Regional Final" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/6/4/WVU_V_UK_Monday_Regional_Final_0813_large.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – Redshirt junior Maxx Yehl of the West Virginia University baseball team was named a finalist for National Pitcher of the Year by the College Baseball Foundation, the organization announced on Thursday.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/4/WVU_V_UK_Monday_Regional_Final_0813_large.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/4/WVU_V_UK_Monday_Regional_Final_0813_large.jpg"><media:title>Maxx Yehl throws a pitch against Kentucky in the NCAA Regional Final</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/4/WVU_V_UK_Monday_Regional_Final_0813_large.jpg" length="1" type="image/jpg" /><pubDate>Thu, 4 Jun 2026 16:00:00 EST</pubDate><s:sport_id>1</s:sport_id><s:story_id>59166</s:story_id></item><item><title>West Virginia Hosts Cal Poly in NCAA Super Regionals</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/4/baseball-west-virginia-hosts-cal-poly-in-ncaa-super-regionals</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/6/4/baseball-west-virginia-hosts-cal-poly-in-ncaa-super-regionals</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="The WVU Baseball Team stands outside the dugout ready to take the field." src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/6/4/WVU_V_UK_Monday-47.jpeg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The West Virginia University baseball team hosts the Cal Poly Mustangs in the NCAA Super Regionals from June 5-7 at Kendrick Family Ballpark in Morgantown.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/4/WVU_V_UK_Monday-47.jpeg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/6/4/WVU_V_UK_Monday-47.jpeg"><media:title>The WVU Baseball Team stands outside the dugout ready to take the field.</media:title></media:content><e